FileAccelerator

25/12/2013
Need to set up environment.  Config file is ~/FileAccelerator/.git/config
url = https://CodePoet1@github.com/CodePoet1/FileAccelerator.git - this will prompt for password when commiting

To receive all files;
	1. set up directory on linux -> mkdir ~/Projects/FileAccelerator
	2. initialise .git/config -> git init
	3. add remote link to github (adds entry to .git/config) -> git remote add origin https://CodePoet1@github.com/CodePoer1/FileAccelerator.git
	4. download files -> git pull origin master



"git remote -v" this will show the status of the push and fetch urls

Step 1
mkdir ~/FileAccelerator
# Creates a directory for your project called "FileAccelerator" in your user directory

cd ~/FileAccelerator
# Changes the current working directory to your newly created directory

git init
# Sets up the necessary Git files
# Initialized empty Git repository in /Users/tony/FileAccelerator/.git/

touch README
# Creates a file called "README" in your FileAccelerator directory

git add README
# Stages your README file, adding it to the list of files to be committed

git commit -m 'first commit'
# Commits your files, adding the message "first commit"

git remote add origin https://CodePoet1@github.com/CodePoet1/FileAccelerator.git
# Creates a remote named "origin" pointing at your GitHub repository

git push origin master
# Sends your commits in the "master" branch to GitHub
